ntsync 1014: lockless list_empty_careful fast-path on SEND_PI boost-target scan

Audio-thread NTSYNC_IOC_CHANNEL_SEND_PI looks up a boost target by
walking ch->u.channel.recv_wq.head under wq->lock.  In the production
configuration the receiver is the gamma audio dispatcher, which since
Phase 3 parks in NTSYNC_IOC_AGGREGATE_WAIT — never in CHANNEL_RECV /
RECV2.  recv_wq is therefore EMPTY for the dispatcher path, and the
spin_lock_irqsave / list_for_each_entry / spin_unlock_irqrestore around
that empty walk is pure overhead on every SEND_PI.

This patch wraps the lock-and-walk in a `list_empty_careful(&wq->head)`
check.  Empty common case: zero lock acquisitions; non-empty case:
identical behaviour to before (lock, walk, unlock).

Correctness
===========

`list_empty_careful` uses `smp_load_acquire(&head->next)` then compares
against `head->prev`.  This is the standard rmb-fenced lockless empty
check used throughout the kernel (cf. wait_queue_active patterns).

wq->head mutators (wait_event_interruptible_exclusive,
prepare_to_wait_exclusive, finish_wait, autoremove_wake_function) all
take wq->lock when modifying head.  Our observation is therefore backed
by a stable model: empty/non-empty answers are coherent with respect to
the lock-protected mutator set.

Best-effort tolerance
=====================

The boost-target lookup is **already explicitly best-effort** — the
existing fall-through to ch->any_waiters (NSPA 1010 + Phase 3+
aggregate-wait support) is the cold-path catch-all.  A racy
list_empty_careful that observes "empty" while a concurrent waiter is
mid-insert results in: skip the boost on this SEND_PI, the next SEND_PI
picks up the now-stable list.  Same race-safety profile as the existing
fall-through path; same precision-not-correctness regression bound.

The wake_up that follows lookup is unaffected — late waiters still get
woken on entry-pop notification.

RT-safety
=========

- Zero new allocations under wq->lock (no allocations under any lock at
  all in this path).
- list_empty_careful is two cache-hot loads + a comparison; nanoseconds
  on the audio thread's SEND_PI critical section.
- When non-empty, behaviour is identical to before — same lock acquire,
  same walk, same unlock.
- No new sleeps, no new atomics, no new barriers beyond
  smp_load_acquire (which is free on x86_64 — release-acquire ordering
  is implied by the load).

Independence
============

This patch is independently revertable from the 1013 dedicated-slab
caches patch.  They touch different code paths (1013: alloc/free across
many sites; 1014: one boost-target-lookup site) and serve different
purposes (1013: cache locality; 1014: lock-acquire elimination).

